sentences: Juthika Roy (20 April 1920 – 5 February 2014) was a Classical and Bhajan (devotional) singer from India.
She was awarded the Padma Shri, the fourth highest civilian award in India, in 1972.

She recorded her first album in 1932, at age 12 years old.
